1
00:00:54,341 --> 00:00:59,841
霍比特人

2
00:01:04,591 --> 00:01:07,143
亲爱的弗罗多
OLD BILBO (V.O.): My dear Frodo.

3
00:01:12,850 --> 00:01:17,371
你曾经问过我是否我把
You asked me once if I had told you everything there was to know about my...

4
00:01:17,387 --> 00:01:18,949
自己的冒险故事全告诉你了
adventures.

5
00:01:19,342 --> 00:01:23,082
我可以诚实地说尽管我说了真相
And while I can honestly say I have told you the truth...

6
00:01:24,119 --> 00:01:27,000
但我没把故事说完整
I may not have told you all of it.

7
00:01:34,185 --> 00:01:36,766
现在我老了，弗罗多
I am old now Frodo.

8
00:01:38,023 --> 00:01:41,238
我不再是以前那个霍比特人了
I'm not the same hobbit I once was.

9
00:01:43,919 --> 00:01:48,651
我想是时候让你知道
I think it is time for you to know...

10
00:01:48,963 --> 00:01:51,689
事情的全貌了
what really happened.

11
00:01:52,889 --> 00:01:55,682
那是很久以前的事
It began long ago.

12
00:01:57,683 --> 00:02:00,348
发生在东方国度之外的土地上
In a land far away to the East.

13
00:02:00,653 --> 00:02:06,490
一个你现在不再可能找到的地方
The like of which you will not find in the world today.

14
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:18,566
那儿有个河谷镇
There was the city of Dale.

15
00:02:18,688 --> 00:02:24,240
它的集市远近闻名，那儿满是精美的物品
Its market's known far and wide, full of the bounties of fine and vail,

16
00:02:24,785 --> 00:02:27,798
一片安宁，繁荣的景象
peaceful and prosperous.

17
00:02:30,656 --> 00:02:36,130
这座城位于中土世界最伟大的王国
For this city laid before the doors of the greatest kingdom in Middle- earth...

18
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:38,910
伊鲁柏前
Erebor.

19
00:02:39,332 --> 00:02:43,616
那是山下国王索尔的要塞
Stronghold of Thrór, king under the mountain.

20
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:46,885
他是最伟大的矮人国王
The mightiest of the dwarf lords.

21
00:02:47,564 --> 00:02:52,832
索尔从不担心自己的统治 从不怀疑王国能否延续
Thrór ruled with utter surety, never doubting his house would endure,

22
00:02:52,903 --> 00:02:56,541
因为王位的继承稳稳地掌握在
for his line lay secure in the lives of his son...

23
00:02:57,259 --> 00:02:58,885
他的儿子和孙子手中
and grandson.

24
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:03,619
弗罗多，
Ah, Frodo. 

25
00:03:03,838 --> 00:03:06,093
伊鲁柏隐藏在深深的大山里
Erebor Built deep within the mountain itself,

26
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:09,727
这座要塞城的美是一个传奇
the beauty of this fortress city was a legend.

27
00:03:10,092 --> 00:03:15,638
它的财富在于土地 在于岩石里开凿出的珍贵宝石
Its wealth lay in the earth, in precious gems humed from rock,

28
00:03:15,802 --> 00:03:21,557
还有像河一样流淌于岩石缝里的金子
and in great seams of gold running like rivers through stone.

29
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,775
矮人的技能无与伦比
The skill of the dwarves was unequaled.

30
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:30,152
能用钻石，绿宝石，红宝石和蓝宝石
Fashioning object of great beauty,

31
00:03:30,834 --> 00:03:35,066
制作精美物品
out of diamond, emerald, ruby and sapphire.

32
00:03:35,909 --> 00:03:39,859
他们越挖越深，挖到深处
Ever they delved deeper down into the dark,

33
00:03:40,269 --> 00:03:43,004
就在那里发现了它
and that is where they found it.

34
00:03:48,945 --> 00:03:51,947
大山之心
The heart of the mountain...

35
00:03:53,243 --> 00:03:55,623
阿肯宝石
The Arkenstone.

36
00:03:56,171 --> 00:03:58,860
索尔叫它“国王宝石”
Thrór named it the king's jewel.

37
00:03:58,993 --> 00:04:03,733
把它作为自己神圣统治权的象征
He took it as a sign, a sign that his right to rule was divine.

38
00:04:04,376 --> 00:04:10,723
所有人都要来朝拜 甚至包括精灵国王瑟兰督伊
All would pay homage to him. Even the great Elven king, Thranduil.

39
00:04:12,046 --> 00:04:16,145
不过安宁和富庶的日子不再延续了
But the years of peace and plenty were not to last.

40
00:04:17,318 --> 00:04:20,488
慢慢地白天变得阴沉
Slowly the days turned sour,

41
00:04:21,234 --> 00:04:23,900
夜晚总是提心吊胆
and the watchful nights closed in.

42
00:04:30,961 --> 00:04:34,577
索尔对金子的爱越发疯狂
Thrór's love of gold had grown too fierce...

43
00:04:36,763 --> 00:04:40,410
内心开始滋生病态
A sickness had begun to grow within him.

44
00:04:41,512 --> 00:04:44,337
那是思想的病变
It was a sickness of the mind.

45
00:04:46,963 --> 00:04:49,773
而病态滋生的地方
And where sickness thrives...

46
00:04:50,351 --> 00:04:53,398
就有恶事相随
bad things will follow.

47
00:05:01,501 --> 00:05:07,108
最先他们听到了来自北方的飓风般的噪音
The first they heard was a noise like a hurricane, coming down from the North.

48
00:05:07,209 --> 00:05:13,100
山上的松树在干热的风中吱嘎响着断裂了
The pines on the mountain creaked and cracked in the hot dry wind.

49
00:05:16,849 --> 00:05:19,745
巴林，放警报
THORIN: Balin, sound the alarm.

50
00:05:22,242 --> 00:05:23,935
叫守卫出来，立马行动！
Call out the guards, do it now!

51
00:05:24,154 --> 00:05:25,482
怎么了？
BALIN: What is it?

52
00:05:25,631 --> 00:05:26,858
龙来了
Dragon.

53
00:05:27,810 --> 00:05:30,284
龙来了！
DRAGON!

54
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:34,980
那是北方来的火龙
OLD BILBO (V.O.): He was a Firedrake from the North.

55
00:05:42,516 --> 00:05:45,648
斯矛戈来了
Smaug... had come!

56
00:06:13,683 --> 00:06:16,829
那日死伤无数
Such wanton death was dealt that day,

57
00:06:17,516 --> 00:06:20,407
因为城里的人都敌不过斯矛戈
for this city of men was nothing to Smaug.

58
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,993
他盯上了另一件宝物
His eye was set on another price.

59
00:06:29,543 --> 00:06:35,603
龙对金子也有邪恶而强烈的欲望
For dragons covet gold... with a dark and fierce desire.

60
00:07:07,707 --> 00:07:09,611
不！
NO!

61
00:07:17,927 --> 00:07:21,017
伊鲁柏灭亡了
Erebor... was lost.

62
00:07:25,558 --> 00:07:30,688
只要恶龙还活着他就会拼命守护掠夺物
For a dragon will guard his plunder as long as he lives.

63
00:07:39,596 --> 00:07:41,242
逃命吧！
Run for your lives!

64
00:07:42,524 --> 00:07:44,148
救救我们！
Help us!

65
00:07:56,791 --> 00:08:01,562
瑟兰督伊不会冒灭族之险与恶龙对抗
Thranduil would not risk the lives of his kin against the lawth of the dragon.

66
00:08:02,572 --> 00:08:05,678
那天精灵没有帮忙
No help came from the Elves that day.

67
00:08:06,431 --> 00:08:09,006
从那之后再也没有
Nor any day since.

68
00:08:10,376 --> 00:08:16,147
丢失了家园的伊鲁柏矮人在荒野里游荡
Robbed of their homeland, the dwarves of Erebor wandered the wilderness.

69
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:20,002
曾经伟大的矮人变得低贱了
The once mighty people brought low.

70
00:08:21,986 --> 00:08:25,413
年轻的矮人王子干自己能找到的活儿
The young dwarf prince took work where he could find it,

71
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:28,012
在人类村落里劳作
laboring in the villages of men.

72
00:08:28,251 --> 00:08:30,553
但他始终记得
But always, he remembered...

73
00:08:30,701 --> 00:08:36,710
月亮下冒烟的大山 如同火炬般烧得通红的树
the mountain smoke beneath the moon, the trees like torches blazing bright,

74
00:08:36,883 --> 00:08:42,919
恶龙在空中喷火，城池烧成灰烬
where he had seen dragon fire in the sky, and a city turn to ash.

75
00:08:44,898 --> 00:08:49,256
他从没原谅过也从没忘记那些事
And he never forgave... and he never forgot.

76
00:08:54,861 --> 00:08:58,669
亲爱的弗罗多，我就是这时掺和进去的
That, my dear Frodo, is where I come in.

77
00:08:59,345 --> 00:09:02,348
算是因为机遇和巫师的意愿
For quite by chance, and the will of a wizard,

78
00:09:02,464 --> 00:09:06,524
命运决定我成为这个传说的一部分
fate decided I would become part of this tale.

79
00:09:07,941 --> 00:09:11,915
故事开始于，就像你期望的那样……
It began... well, it began as you might expect.

80
00:09:13,635 --> 00:09:18,289
地上的一个洞里，那里住着个霍比特人
In a hole in the ground, there lived a hobbit.

81
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:25,314
不是个肮脏，恶心 满是虫子和软泥臭味的湿洞
Not a nasty, dirty wet hole full of worms and oozy smells.

82
00:09:25,955 --> 00:09:27,775
这是霍比特人的家
This was a hobbit home.

83
00:09:28,356 --> 00:09:32,955
那意味着好食物，温暖的
And that means good food, a warm house...

84
00:09:34,119 --> 00:09:36,468
舒适的家
and all the comforts of home.

85
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:12,733
谢谢
OLD BILBO: Thank you.

86
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:15,136
这是什么？
FRODO: What's this?

87
00:10:15,286 --> 00:10:18,744
这是隐私，把你黏糊糊的爪子拿开！
That is private. Keep your sticky paws off!

88
00:10:19,948 --> 00:10:21,859
还没准备好呢
It's not ready yet.

89
00:10:22,148 --> 00:10:23,958
准备好什么？
Not ready for what?

90
00:10:24,053 --> 00:10:25,521
给人看
Reading.

91
00:10:28,552 --> 00:10:30,651
这些到底是什么？
OLD BILBO: What on earth are these?

92
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:33,672
聚会邀请的回复
FRODO: Replies to the party invitations.

93
00:10:34,914 --> 00:10:36,403
天哪！
Good gracious.

94
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:38,436
是今天吗？
Is it today?

95
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:41,405
他们都说会来，除了萨克维尔巴金斯家
They all say they're coming, except for the Sackville- Bagginses,

96
00:10:41,585 --> 00:10:43,717
他们要你亲自去请
who're demanding you ask them in person.

97
00:10:43,799 --> 00:10:46,929
真的吗？除非我死了
OLD BILBO: Are they, indeed. Over my dead body.

98
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,999
他们或许觉得这可以接受
They'd probably find that quite agreeable.

99
00:10:49,203 --> 00:10:51,614
他们似乎觉得你的地道里充满金子
They seem to think you have tunnels overflowing with gold.

100
00:10:51,663 --> 00:10:55,107
只是一小箱，压根儿满不上来
It was one small chest, hardly overflowing.

101
00:10:56,318 --> 00:10:58,300
还有巨怪的臭味
And it still smells of troll.

102
00:10:59,275 --> 00:11:01,054
你到底在干什么？
What on earth are you doing?

103
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:05,416
做防备！
Taking precautions!

104
00:11:06,101 --> 00:11:08,700
有一回我逮到她偷银器
You know I caught her making off with the silverware once.

105
00:11:08,802 --> 00:11:09,841
谁？
FRODO: Who?

106
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:12,460
罗贝拉・萨克维尔巴金斯
OLD BILBO: Lobelia Sackville- Baggins.

107
00:11:13,015 --> 00:11:16,171
她把我的勺子全装在口袋里
She had all my spoons stuffed in her pockets.

108
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:18,057
可怕的女人
Dreadful woman.

109
00:11:18,292 --> 00:11:20,979
盯紧她，等我……
Make sure you keep an eye on her after I'm...

110
00:11:22,573 --> 00:11:24,393
等我……
When I'm... when...

111
00:11:25,062 --> 00:11:27,135
等你什么？
When you're... what?

112
00:11:31,245 --> 00:11:34,545
没什么，没什么
It's nothing... nothing.

113
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:42,167
有些人开始琢磨你
FRODO: You know, some people are beginning to wonder about you.

114
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,216
他们觉得你变得很奇怪
They think you're becoming odd.

115
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:47,122
奇怪？
C Odd? C Hmm...

116
00:11:48,156 --> 00:11:49,450
不爱交际
Unsociable.

117
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:52,106
我不爱交际？胡扯
Unsociable, me? Nonsense.

118
00:11:52,384 --> 00:11:54,669
做个好孩子，把这个钉在大门上
Be a good lad and put that on the gate.

119
00:12:04,755 --> 00:12:06,550
你觉得他会来吗？
Do you think he will come?

120
00:12:06,650 --> 00:12:07,530
谁？
Who?

121
00:12:07,757 --> 00:12:08,733
甘道夫
Gandalf.

122
00:12:08,873 --> 00:12:12,511
他不会错过放巫师烟花的机会的
Oh, he wouldn't miss a chance to let off his wiz poppers.

123
00:12:12,668 --> 00:12:15,040
他会上演一出好戏的，等着吧
He'll give us quite a show, you'll see.

124
00:12:15,181 --> 00:12:16,094
那么我走了
FRODO: Right then. I am off. .

125
00:12:16,095 --> 00:12:17,110
去哪儿？
FRODO: Right then. I am off. C Off to where?

126
00:12:17,238 --> 00:12:19,499
东域森林，我要去给他惊喜
FRODO: Eastfarthing woods. I'm going to surprise him.

127
00:12:19,618 --> 00:12:22,877
去吧，你不会愿意迟到的
OLD BILBO: Well go on then. You don't want to be late.

128
00:12:27,433 --> 00:12:30,123
他不批准迟到
OLD BILBO: He doesn't approve being late.

129
00:12:31,327 --> 00:12:33,285
我也不
Not that I ever was.

130
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:36,614
那些日子，我总是很准时
In those days, I was always on time.

131
00:12:37,350 --> 00:12:40,191
我受人尊敬
I was entirely respectable...

132
00:12:41,504 --> 00:12:44,584
从没发生过
and nothing unexpected...

133
00:12:45,826 --> 00:12:47,756
意外的事
ever happened.

134
00:12:50,738 --> 00:12:54,683
意外旅程
AN UNEXPECTED JOURNEY

135
00:13:06,683 --> 00:13:08,683
（60年前）

136
00:13:11,518 --> 00:13:14,268
- 早上好 - 什么意思？
C Good morning. C What do you mean?

137
00:13:14,322 --> 00:13:15,699
你是在向我问好
Do you mean to wish me a good morning,

138
00:13:15,707 --> 00:13:18,895
还是想说不论我是否喜欢，这个早上都还不错？
or do you mean that it is a good morning whether I want it or not?

139
00:13:20,121 --> 00:13:24,421
或者是想说在这个特别的早上你感觉不错？
Or perhaps you mean to say that you feel good on this particular morning...

140
00:13:24,952 --> 00:13:28,981
或者你只是在说这是个值得过的早上？
or are you simply stating that this is a morning to be good on?

141
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:32,880
我想全都有
All of them at once, I suppose.

142
00:13:39,676 --> 00:13:40,846
要我帮忙吗？
Can I help you?

143
00:13:40,995 --> 00:13:42,815
看看再说
It remains to be seen.

144
00:13:44,838 --> 00:13:48,835
我在找人和我一起冒险
I'm looking for someone to share in an adventure.

145
00:13:52,121 --> 00:13:53,509
冒险？
An adventure?

146
00:13:55,634 --> 00:13:58,082
不，我不认为布理以西的任何人
No, I don't imagine anyone west of Bree,

147
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,546
会对冒险有兴趣
who'd have much interest in adventures.

148
00:14:01,246 --> 00:14:05,352
那是恶心，烦人，不舒服的事
Nasty, disturbing... uncomfortable things.

149
00:14:06,283 --> 00:14:07,978
还会让你来不及吃晚餐
Make you late for dinner!

150
00:14:16,959 --> 00:14:17,727
早上好！
Good morning!

151
00:14:17,784 --> 00:14:22,961
真没想到竟然让贝拉多娜・图克的儿子
To think that I should have lived to be good- morninged by Belladonna Took's son,

152
00:14:23,125 --> 00:14:25,467
把我当成门口卖扣子的小贩来问早！
as if I was selling buttons at the door!

153
00:14:26,603 --> 00:14:27,702
再说一遍？
Beg your pardon?

154
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:31,832
你变了，并非完全变好，比尔博・巴金斯
You've changed, and not entirely for the better, Bilbo Baggins.

155
00:14:32,023 --> 00:14:33,090
抱歉，我认识你吗？
I'm sorry, do I know you?

156
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:36,274
你或许记得我的名字 只是不记得我就是那个人
Would you know my name, although you don't remember I belong to it,

157
00:14:36,337 --> 00:14:38,155
我是甘道夫
I'm Gandalf...

158
00:14:38,397 --> 00:14:40,217
甘道夫意味着……
and Gandalf means...

159
00:14:42,543 --> 00:14:43,663
我！
me!

160
00:14:44,678 --> 00:14:48,675
就是那个造美丽烟花的游荡巫师甘道夫？
Not Gandalf, the wandering wizard who made such excellent fireworks,

161
00:14:48,715 --> 00:14:51,871
老图克在仲夏节前夜都会放你的烟花！
Old Took used to have them on Midsummer's Eve!

162
00:14:53,047 --> 00:14:55,502
我不知道你还在做买卖
I had no idea you were still in business.

163
00:14:55,984 --> 00:14:57,451
我还能做什么？
And where else should I be?

164
00:14:57,499 --> 00:14:59,850
呃……
Well...

165
00:15:02,179 --> 00:15:05,898
我很高兴你记起了我的一些事
Well, I'm pleased to find you remember something about me...

166
00:15:06,245 --> 00:15:08,742
即便只是我的烟花
even if it's only my fireworks.

167
00:15:10,383 --> 00:15:12,232
那么就决定了
So that's decided.

168
00:15:12,436 --> 00:15:14,419
这对你来说很不错
It will be very good for you...

169
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:19,167
对我来说也很有趣，我去通知其他人
and most amusing for me. I shall inform the others.

170
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:22,475
通知谁，什么，不，不，不，等等
Inform the who- what- no, no. No, wait.

171
00:15:22,819 --> 00:15:28,043
我们这儿不要冒险，谢谢，不是今天，不是……
We do not want any adventures here, thank you- not today, not...

172
00:15:28,616 --> 00:15:32,989
我建议你去山那边或湖那边试试
I suggest you try over the hill or... across the water.

173
00:15:35,663 --> 00:15:37,035
早上好
Good morning.

174
00:16:53,335 --> 00:16:54,863
[Bell rings]

175
00:16:59,954 --> 00:17:01,279
德瓦林
Dwalin...

176
00:17:01,983 --> 00:17:03,662
为您效劳
at your service.

177
00:17:03,777 --> 00:17:05,504
Hm... Uh...

178
00:17:06,619 --> 00:17:08,960
比尔博……巴金斯……
Bilbo... Baggins...

179
00:17:10,171 --> 00:17:12,702
听候吩咐，我们认识吗？
at yours. But do we know each other?

180
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:14,820
不认识
No.

181
00:17:16,323 --> 00:17:17,922
哪边，伙计？
Which way, laddie?

182
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:19,279
就在这下面吗？
Is it down here?

183
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:21,248
什么在什么下边？
Is it down here? C Is- Is what? Down where?

184
00:17:21,891 --> 00:17:25,888
晚餐，他说会有晚餐，还很丰盛
Supper. He said there'd be food. Lots of it.

185
00:17:26,414 --> 00:17:29,418
他……他说？谁说的？
He- he said? Who said?

186
00:17:40,165 --> 00:17:42,436
很棒的菜，还有吗？
Very good dish. Any more?

187
00:17:43,475 --> 00:17:46,405
什么？噢，有，有
What? Uh, oh, uh yes, yes.

188
00:17:53,039 --> 00:17:54,057
请便
Help yourself.

189
00:17:58,404 --> 00:17:59,995
只不过是，呃……
It's just that, hum...

190
00:18:00,404 --> 00:18:02,535
我没想有人来陪吃
I wasn't expecting company.

191
00:18:02,972 --> 00:18:04,372
[Bell rings]

192
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:07,747
门铃响了
That would be the door.

193
00:18:12,249 --> 00:18:14,902
巴林，为您效劳
Balin... at your service.

194
00:18:16,082 --> 00:18:17,180
晚上好
Good evening.

195
00:18:17,331 --> 00:18:18,859
对，对，是个好天
Yes, yes it is.

196
00:18:19,797 --> 00:18:21,497
不过我想晚些或许会下雨
Though I thing it might rain later.

197
00:18:22,295 --> 00:18:23,695
我迟到了吗？
Am I late?

198
00:18:24,217 --> 00:18:25,966
迟到……什么？
Late... for what?

199
00:18:26,518 --> 00:18:28,869
Ooh! Ah ah!

200
00:18:29,162 --> 00:18:30,769
晚上好，兄弟！
Evening, brother!

201
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,301
[Balin aughing]

202
00:18:32,505 --> 00:18:34,229
天哪！
By my beard!

203
00:18:34,651 --> 00:18:37,642
你比上回我们见面时还矮还壮
You are shorter and wider than last we met.

204
00:18:37,886 --> 00:18:39,706
壮了，没矮
Wider, not shorter.

205
00:18:40,102 --> 00:18:42,365
足以扛住我们两人合力
Sharp enough for both of us.

206
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,116
[Balin laughing]

207
00:18:50,093 --> 00:18:51,528
[Both laughing]

208
00:18:51,676 --> 00:18:54,608
对不起，抱歉，我不想插话
Uh... Excuse me. Sorry. I hate to interrupt.

209
00:18:54,702 --> 00:18:58,529
但问题是我不太确定你们走对门了
Uh, but the thing is I'm not entirely sure you're in the right house.

210
00:18:58,678 --> 00:18:59,787
你吃了没？
BALIN: Have you eaten?

211
00:18:59,798 --> 00:19:01,668
不是说我不好客
It- It's not that I don't like visitors.

212
00:19:01,793 --> 00:19:05,175
我和其他霍比特人一样好客
I like visitors as much as the next hobbit.

213
00:19:05,353 --> 00:19:08,468
但我希望在他们来……拜访之前 我就认识他们了……
But I do like to know them before they come... visiting...

214
00:19:08,624 --> 00:19:09,788
- 这是什么？ - 不知道
C DWALIN: What's this? C BALIN: I don't know,

215
00:19:09,796 --> 00:19:11,356
我想是奶酪
BALIN: I just thought it a cheese,

216
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:12,424
- 问题是…… - 变蓝了
C BILBO: The thing is- C BALIN: Gone blue.

217
00:19:12,448 --> 00:19:14,102
- 都是孔，但是发霉了 - 问题是……
C DWALIN: It's riddled, but mold. C BILBO: the thing is,

218
00:19:14,329 --> 00:19:18,030
我不……我不知道怎么开始……完全不懂
BILBO: I don't- I don't know how to begin. Not in the slightest.

219
00:19:18,694 --> 00:19:22,613
我不想太直接，但我…… 我得说自己的想法，抱歉
BILBO: I don't mean to be blunt, but I- but I had to speak my mind. I'm sorry.

220
00:19:26,461 --> 00:19:27,811
接受道歉
Apology accepted.

221
00:19:28,326 --> 00:19:30,300
不，填满，兄弟，别吝啬
BALIN: Oh no, fill it up brother, don't stint.

222
00:19:30,396 --> 00:19:31,796
[Bell rings]

223
00:19:32,275 --> 00:19:34,375
如果你坚持的话，我可以再吃一次
BALIN: I could eat again, if you insist.

224
00:19:36,729 --> 00:19:38,705
- 菲力 - 奇力
C Fíli. C and Kíli.

225
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:40,539
为您效劳
At your service.

226
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,541
您肯定是巴金斯先生
You most be Mr. Boggins.

227
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:44,963
不，你们不能进来，来错地方了
No! You can't come in, you've come to the wrong house.

228
00:19:45,016 --> 00:19:47,049
你……取消了吗？
What's you- Has it been canceled?

229
00:19:47,127 --> 00:19:48,525
没人告诉我们
No one told us.

230
00:19:48,882 --> 00:19:50,489
可以……不，没什么被取消了
Can-  No, nothing's been canceled.

231
00:19:50,521 --> 00:19:51,997
放心了
That's a relief.

232
00:19:55,608 --> 00:19:58,816
小心点，我们刚磨过这些
Careful with these, we just had them sharpened.

233
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:01,288
这个地方很美
It's nice, this place.

234
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:02,460
你自己建的吗？
Did you do it yourself?

235
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:04,545
不，一直属于家族所有
BILBO: Well no, it's been in the family for years.

236
00:20:04,819 --> 00:20:07,724
那是我母亲的嫁妆盒，你能不那么做吗？
That's my mother's glory box, can you please not do that?

237
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:10,272
菲力，奇力，过来，帮帮忙
DWALIN: Fíli, Kíli come on, give us a hand.

238
00:20:10,538 --> 00:20:11,801
德瓦林先生
Mr. Dwalin.

239
00:20:13,957 --> 00:20:16,837
我们把这个推进洞里，不然坐不下所有人
BALIN: Let's shove this in the hole, or otherwise we'll never get everyone in.

240
00:20:17,009 --> 00:20:19,095
大家？你们还有多少人？
BILBO: Hey- Everyone? How many more of you?

241
00:20:19,236 --> 00:20:20,285
你们要什么？
What do you want? .

242
00:20:20,286 --> 00:20:21,444
你们要什么？噢，不
What do you want? C Oh no.

243
00:20:22,314 --> 00:20:24,194
不，不，没人在家
No, no. There's nobody home!

244
00:20:24,885 --> 00:20:27,602
滚开！烦其他人去
Go away! And... bother somebody else.

245
00:20:27,884 --> 00:20:30,827
我的客厅里已经有太多矮人了
There's far too many dwarves in my dining room as it is.

246
00:20:31,155 --> 00:20:34,426
如果……如果这是某个蠢货的玩笑主意
If-  if this is some... blunt head's idea of a joke,

247
00:20:35,262 --> 00:20:39,353
我只能说，非常……没品位！
I can only say, it is in very... poor taste!

248
00:20:41,509 --> 00:20:43,906
把你的手拿开，大蠢驴！
A DWARF: Put your hands off, you big lump!

249
00:20:48,754 --> 00:20:50,095
甘道夫
Gandalf.

250
00:20:50,264 --> 00:20:52,785
那些是我的，抱歉，别拿我的酒！
BILBO: Those are my fr- Excuse me, not my wine!

251
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,563
把那放回去
Put that back.

252
00:20:53,914 --> 00:20:54,743
把那放回去
Put that back!

253
00:20:54,758 --> 00:20:56,976
别拿果酱，谢谢，抱歉，抱歉
Not the jam, please. Excuse me. Ex-  Excuse me.

254
00:20:57,014 --> 00:20:59,451
太多了点吧？你有奶酪刀吗？
A tad excessive, isn't it? Have you got a cheese knife?

255
00:20:59,470 --> 00:21:02,256
奶酪刀？他总是一大块一大块地吃
BOFUR: A cheese knife? He eats it by the block.

256
00:21:03,209 --> 00:21:04,964
不，不，那是蒙戈爷爷的椅子，不
No no, that's grandpa Mungo's chair, no-

257
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:07,066
就这样，拿回去，拜托，拿回去
ah, so is that. Take it back, please. Take it back,

258
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,814
这是古董，不是用来坐的，谢谢
this is antique, not for sitting on. Thank you.

259
00:21:11,072 --> 00:21:13,468
那是书，不是杯托
BILBO: That is a book, not a coaster.

260
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:15,507
呃，把地图放下
BILBO: Uh, put that map down.

261
00:21:16,719 --> 00:21:18,615
- 抱歉，甘道夫先生 - 什么事？
C DORI: Excuse me, Mr. Gandalf. C Yes?

262
00:21:18,746 --> 00:21:21,443
我能给你倒杯甘菊茶吗？
May I tempt you with a cup of camomile?

263
00:21:21,607 --> 00:21:25,503
不了，谢谢，朵力，给我来点红酒吧
Ooh, no thank you Dori, a little red wine... for me I think.

264
00:21:33,577 --> 00:21:35,817
菲力，奇力
GANDALF: Uh, Fíli, Kíli, uh...

265
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:40,635
奎林，葛罗林，德瓦林，巴林
óin, Glóin... Dwalin, Balin...

266
00:21:40,776 --> 00:21:42,127
比弗，波弗，庞柏
Bifur, Bofur, Bombur...

267
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:43,133
- 朵力，诺力 - 不，不
C Dori, Nori... C BILBO: No, no,

268
00:21:43,157 --> 00:21:44,443
别拿我的番茄干，谢谢
BILBO: not my dried tomatoes, thank you.

269
00:21:44,475 --> 00:21:46,300
- 欧力！ - 不，谢谢
C GANDALF: Ori! C No, thank you.

270
00:21:47,301 --> 00:21:49,418
[Bifur speaks dwarvish]

271
00:21:49,670 --> 00:21:51,770
对，你说得对，比弗
GANDALF: Yes you are quite right, Bifur.

272
00:21:52,512 --> 00:21:54,879
我们似乎少了一个矮人
We appear to be one dwarf short.

273
00:21:54,959 --> 00:21:56,402
他迟到了，就这样
He is late, is all.

274
00:21:56,484 --> 00:21:59,731
他到北方参加我们的家族会议，他会来的
He travel North to a meeting of our kin, he will come.

275
00:22:00,724 --> 00:22:01,826
甘道夫先生
C DORI: Mr. Gandalf? C Hmm?

276
00:22:01,865 --> 00:22:07,007
按您要求，一点儿红酒，有水果的香味
A little glass of red wine as requested, it's got a fruity bouquet.

277
00:22:07,796 --> 00:22:08,855
干杯
Cheers.

278
00:22:14,950 --> 00:22:17,627
[Big talking noise]

279
00:22:20,287 --> 00:22:21,995
- 巴林 - 接住！
C Balin- C Catch!

280
00:22:35,972 --> 00:22:38,220
谁想要麦芽酒？拿去
Who wants an ale? There you go.

281
00:22:39,725 --> 00:22:41,235
我再喝一杯
OIN: Let me have another drink.

282
00:22:41,275 --> 00:22:42,675
拿去
BALIN: Here you go.

283
00:22:47,304 --> 00:22:49,124
数到三！
Hey, on the count of three!

284
00:22:49,289 --> 00:22:50,997
一！二！
One! Two!

285
00:22:51,037 --> 00:22:52,157
来吧！
Come!

286
00:22:57,671 --> 00:23:02,246
[They belch]

287
00:23:04,288 --> 00:23:07,851
抱歉，那是桌巾，不是抹布
Ex-  Excuse me, that is a doily, not a dish cloth.

288
00:23:07,918 --> 00:23:08,900
上面都是洞！
BOFUR: But it's full of holes!

289
00:23:08,924 --> 00:23:11,004
就该长成这样，这是钩针编织的
BILBO: It's supposed to look like that, it's crochet.

290
00:23:11,029 --> 00:23:13,829
如果拿几个球来，这还是个好游戏呢
Oh, and a wonderful game it is too, if you got the balls for it.

291
00:23:14,113 --> 00:23:16,113
这些惹祸的，烦人的矮人们！
Bebother and confusticate these dwarves!

292
00:23:16,325 --> 00:23:19,299
我亲爱的比尔博，到底怎么回事了？
GANDALF: My dear Bilbo, what on earth is the matter?

293
00:23:19,588 --> 00:23:20,898
怎么回事？
What's the matter?

294
00:23:21,055 --> 00:23:24,062
我被矮人包围了，他们在这里做什么？
I am surrounded by dwarves. What they're doing here?

295
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:28,181
他们在聚会……一旦你习惯了他们
Oh, they're quite a merry gathering... once you get used to 'em.

296
00:23:28,205 --> 00:23:30,132
我不想习惯他们
I don't want to get used to them.

297
00:23:30,178 --> 00:23:33,226
看看我的厨房！地毯上都是泥
Look at the state of my kitchen! There's mud trodding the carpet,

298
00:23:33,297 --> 00:23:35,576
他们……他们抢光了食物
they-  they've pillaged the pantry,

299
00:23:35,623 --> 00:23:37,730
我还不想说他们在厕所里干的事
I'm not even gonna tell you what they've done in the bathroom,

300
00:23:37,738 --> 00:23:39,034
他们把水管全搞坏了！
they've all but destroyed the plumbing!

301
00:23:39,058 --> 00:23:41,238
我不明白他们在我家里做什么！
I don't understand what they're doing in my house!

302
00:23:41,585 --> 00:23:44,739
抱歉，打断一下
ORI: Excuse me, I'm sorry to interrupt.

303
00:23:45,046 --> 00:23:47,075
我要怎么处理盘子？
But what sha'd do with my plate?

304
00:23:47,302 --> 00:23:48,793
这里，欧力，给我
FILI: Here you go, Ori, give it to me.

305
00:23:55,504 --> 00:23:56,624
抱歉！
Excuse me!

306
00:23:56,682 --> 00:24:00,575
那是我母亲的西域陶器，有上百年历史了！
That's my mother's Westfarthing pottery, it's over a hundred years old!

307
00:24:01,281 --> 00:24:03,381
[Doing music with kitchenware]

308
00:24:03,828 --> 00:24:06,677
你们能，能不那么做吗？会磨钝的！
BILBO: And-  and ca-  can you not do that, you'll blunt them!

309
00:24:06,724 --> 00:24:08,995
听到了吗，伙计们？
Ooh, d'you hear that, lads?

310
00:24:09,237 --> 00:24:11,776
他说我们会把刀磨钝！
He says we'll blunt the knives!

311
00:24:11,807 --> 00:24:14,273
?磨钝刀子，压弯叉子
? Blunt the knives, bend the forks,

312
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:16,718
?打破瓶子，烧掉塞子
? Smash the bottles and burn the corks,

313
00:24:16,797 --> 00:24:20,162
?砸碎杯子，折断盘子
? Chip the glasses and crack the plates,

314
00:24:20,225 --> 00:24:22,115
?那就是比尔博・巴金斯讨厌的事！
? That's what Bilbo Baggins hates!

315
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:24,027
?剪破桌布，踩踏黄油
? Cut the cloth and tread on the fat,

316
00:24:24,053 --> 00:24:25,956
?把骨头丢在卧室门垫上
? Leave the bones on the bedroom-mat,

317
00:24:25,974 --> 00:24:29,917
?把牛奶倒在储物室地上
? Pour the milk on the pantry-floor,

318
00:24:30,012 --> 00:24:31,921
?把红酒泼洒到每扇门上
? Splash the wine on every door,

319
00:24:31,985 --> 00:24:33,712
?把坛子倒进炙热的盆里
? Dump the crocks in a boiling bowl,

320
00:24:33,741 --> 00:24:35,725
?拿根大杆来把它们打碎
? Pound them up with a thumping pole,

321
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:40,718
?等你完成若还有完整的
? When you've finished, if any are whole,

322
00:24:40,794 --> 00:24:43,721
?把它们丢到客厅里去滚
? Send them down the hall to roll!

323
00:24:50,536 --> 00:24:53,238
?那就是比尔博・巴金斯讨厌的事！
? That's what Bilbo Baggins hates!

324
00:24:53,396 --> 00:24:57,682
[All dwarves laughing loud]

325
00:24:59,577 --> 00:25:01,677
[Somebody hits the door hard]

326
00:25:06,731 --> 00:25:07,851
他来了
He's here.

327
00:25:12,546 --> 00:25:13,879
甘道夫
Gandalf.

328
00:25:15,722 --> 00:25:18,153
我记得你说这地方好找
I thought you said this place would be easy to find.

329
00:25:18,439 --> 00:25:20,428
我迷了两次路
I lost my way, twice.

330
00:25:20,639 --> 00:25:23,663
要不是门上的标记，我根本找不到
I wouldn't have found it at all, had it not been for that mark on the door.

331
00:25:23,789 --> 00:25:27,053
标记？门上没标记，那是一周前粉刷的
BILBO: Mark? There's no mark on that door, it was painted a week ago!

332
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:29,900
那儿有标记，我自己画上去的
GANDALF: There is a mark, I have put it there myself.

333
00:25:31,191 --> 00:25:35,290
比尔博・巴金斯，请允许我介绍我们的头儿
Bilbo Baggins, allow me to introduce the leader of our company,

334
00:25:35,829 --> 00:25:37,694
索林・橡木盾
Thorin Oakenshield.

335
00:25:37,997 --> 00:25:39,201
那么……
So...

336
00:25:40,905 --> 00:25:42,262
这就是那个霍比特人
This is the hobbit.

337
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:46,391
告诉我巴金斯先生，你经常打仗吗？
Tell me Mr. Baggins, have you done much fighting?

338
00:25:46,445 --> 00:25:47,123
抱歉
Pardon me?

339
00:25:47,139 --> 00:25:50,106
斧头或剑，你用哪个武器？
Axe or sword, what's your weapon of choice?

340
00:25:50,292 --> 00:25:53,602
如果你想知道的话 我倒是有些康克戏的技能
Well, I do have some skill at conkers, if you must know.

341
00:25:53,766 --> 00:25:57,490
但我没弄懂……那有什么关联
But I fail to see... why that's relevant.

342
00:25:57,814 --> 00:25:59,186
我也这么想
I thought as much.

343
00:25:59,648 --> 00:26:02,122
他不像小偷，倒像是杂货商
He looks more like a grocer than a burglar.

344
00:26:02,216 --> 00:26:03,616
[LAUGHS]

345
00:26:07,774 --> 00:26:09,896
伊瑞德隆会议有什么消息？
